                Post:</b></font></td>
            </tr>
	
	        
	 
	        <tr>
              <td width="100%" bgcolor="CDCD9C">
                &nbsp;
                <div align="center">
                  <center>
                  <table border="0" width="98%" cellspacing="1" bgcolor="000000" cellpadding="2">
				  
				    <tr>
                      <td width="6%" valign="top" align="center" bgcolor="bfbf80" background=""><font face="arial" color="4a0000" size="3"><b>1.</b></font></td>
                      <td width="94%" valign="top" bgcolor="CDCD9C"><font face="arial" size="2"><b>Response from:
                        <a href="mailto:dantes@eqrealms.com"><font color="ca0000">Dantes</font></a></b>
                        </font><font face="arial" size="1"> - Friday, Jun 16, 2000 at 3:20 PM</font><font face="arial" size="2"><br>
						
						
						I don't really like the fact that trade skills are being included in newer quests, it's kind of a quick fix because trade skills are useless and Verant is noticing that people are just not using them because of how worthless they are for profit.  So they implement them into quests FORCING people to learn the trade and spend tons of plat on it.<p>Smithing is not profitable and never will be as far as I know.  If they had implemented Armor Repair and the ability to craft magical armor, or implemented some form of Smithing involved in every class armor quest the smithies might actually be able to get paid something.<p>Jewelcraft can earn lots of money but it takes tons of plat to learn, also most folks who practice this trade and enchanters and by the time they are high enough in the skill to produce great jewelry they are already making money hand over fist from items they are a much needed group member in high level dungeons.  They usually end up giving jewelry free to guildmates.<p>As far as the rest of the skills I don't have much experience with them so I won't comment, but I have never really NEEDED anything besides Banded and Jewelry, no other trade skill has produced anything I needed. And now banded is basically a level 1 set of armor since Bronze is so easy to come by and so many sets of it are on the servers.  What ever happened to plans to allow plate armor to be created with smithing? They never implemented that.  They added a few useless weapons, I never see anyone ask for them to be made or even selling them.
						
						</font>
					  </td>
                    </tr>
					 
					
				    <tr>
                      <td width="6%" valign="top" align="center" bgcolor="bfbf80" background=""><font face="arial" color="4a0000" size="3"><b>2.</b></font></td>
