						Well since enchanters can enchant metals and jewelry why cant they enchant armors and weapons? why not enchanter PW armor and other such items. it would make tailering and blacksmithing more profitable. It falls into the spell line for enchanters IMHO. then why not make some more usefull items. (other than jewelcrafting.) trade skills are useless. why have banded when you can have bronze? why have a raw silk robe when you can have an FBR easy enough. I think it would just make sense for smiths to be able to make platemail. WHY NOT? Ulan meadowgreen is a smith and he makes crafted.<p>here is my opinion. get a gem. enchant the mold or one of the components to the armor. bam.just like jewel crafting what jew you combine adds that stat to the piece. then have some of the gems have nice AC bonus. add a metal bar for extra skils. like a platinum bar would make platinum platemail. add an amber and you have and you have platinum amber BP. just my opinion. even if you arent an enchanter just have an enchanter enchant what ever you need then hit combine. <p>i play an enchanter and i know i would love this. not to mention it fits into our line of spells. i know i would enchant something for free. =) 
						
